reporting-org.narrative: The Global Fund to Fight AIDS, Tuberculosis and Malaria

title.narrative: Contribution to universal access of DRC population to effective and impactful interventions against malaria

description.narrative: Congo (Democratic Republic) - Malaria - SANRU Asbl - SANRU. This program has the following goals: To reduce human and socio-economic burden caused by malaria. To reduce malaria mortality and morbidity rates by 40% in 2020, compared with 2015. The objectives of this program are: To protect at least 80% of the population with effective malaria prevention interventions by 2020. To provide parasitological diagnosis targeting 80% of suspected malaria cases and provide prompt and. To increase awareness and knowledge of at least 75% of the population on malaria prevention and control so as to improve uptake and correct use of all interventions by 2020. To strengthen surveillance and M&E systems by 2020. To strengthen program management by 2020
